President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. spoke with Amir Sheikh Tamim Bin Hamad Al-Thani of Qatar regarding the ongoing war in Gaza and their efforts to secure the release of remaining hostages held by Hamas. They emphasized that a hostage deal is crucial for a humanitarian pause in the fighting and to ensure aid reaches those in need. Both leaders expressed the urgency of the situation and praised the collaboration between their teams. They pledged to remain involved until all hostages are reunited with their families and reiterated their shared vision of a peaceful Middle East.